      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHATTANOOGA (1) turned in a better effort at Ballarat last start, finishing second behind Hatari (25.33) in a Grade 4/5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Goes very well from this draw with three wins and two minor placings from six starts. Sure to be about the mark. ULENTA BALE (3) missed the frame latest but had been racing well prior to that including a Grade 5 win two back (29.56) at Sandown. Well placed here and can atone this time. CHAMPLAIN (6) latest effort finished 5th on March 21 over 525m at this track behind Mepunga Express beaten 6 lengths (30.51) in a Grade 4/5. Can feature in the finish. ROWDY BOY (4) is one of the chances after a minor prize in a tight go last start.",
